body: We're currently launching a new devtools server when opening the embedded browser, but for bazel projects it is faster to use the existing devtools server.

comment_data.body: why is there a 15 second timeout?
discussing offline if there is a more robust way to achieve the same result. I worry about all the extra edge cases this could introduce.
I can't remember what we decided on this - keep it? Otherwise it could wait indefinitely without raising an exception.

I tried passing an app through to this function, but it's kind of complicated. There are a couple issues:
- App has to be found this way when opening devtools from the run/debug tab, and this function is used from that workflow
- App doesn't exist when a test is running, but I think we still want to be able to open devtools for bazel projects during tests? I'm not sure about the best way to make requests to the daemon from a test.
This code still has the problem that we are finding all FlutterApps for the project and picking one rather than usinig the app for the app being debugged. Can we pick the right app?
Ah yeah, I can pass the app from where `OpenDevToolsAction` is created.

commit.message: Use existing devtools for bazel in panel
Use isPresent instead of isEmpty for java 8
Get server each time app is restarted
